Surinder,

This warning is printed when there is a discontinuity in the NASA 
polynomial fits at the midpoint temperature.  As you have found, this 
can lead to convergence problems of some algorithms at the midpoint 
temperature.  The best thing to do is to modify the polynomial 
coefficients very slightly to make cp/R and h/RT continuous. 
Alternatively, you can simply avoid using methods like setState_UV 
(which iterates using Newton&#39;s method) very close to the midpoint 
temperature.

Dave



